Mako guda bayan jaridar kasar Sin ta buga wata kasida mai shafi hudu a jaridar Amurka, tana mai cewa cinikayya tsakanin Sin da Amurka na da amfani, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump a ranar Laraba ya ambaci jaridar China Daily da ke cikin jaridar Des Moines Register  mafi yawan sayarwa a jihar Iowa  bayan da ya zargi China da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa China ta yi kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fada wa kamfanin dillancin labarai na Reuters, cewa wani sabon mataki ne na matsin lamba da Washington ke yi wa China.
Duk da yake sanya tallace-tallace daga gwamnatocin kasashen waje al'ada ce ta bunkasa kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington sun shiga cikin yakin cinikayya wanda ya haifar da sanya haraji kan shigo da kaya.
Masu bincike a Amurka da China sun ce an sanya harajin ne don cutar da masu fitar da kayayyaki kamar 'yan kasuwa a Iowa da ke goyon bayan Trump.
Terry Branstead, jakadan Amurka a China da tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayan gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da 'yan kasuwa.
"A yanzu, China ta sake yin kokari wajen buga talla a jaridarmu ta 'yanci".
"A yada farfagandarsu, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin fadin albarka da kuma' yan jarida masu' yanci ta hanyar buga talla a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register", in ji Branstead.
"Amma idan ka duba a kantunan jaridu a Beijing, ba za ka ga yawan 'a'a' ba, kuma ba za ka ga ainihin nuna ra'ayoyin da wasu 'yan kasar Sin ke da shi ba game da yanayin tattalin arzikin kasar, idan aka yi la'akari da cewa jaridar tana karkashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin".
Ya kara da cewa, "daya daga cikin manyan jaridun kasar Sin ya ki amincewa da tayin" na buga labarinsa, ko da yake bai ambaci sunan jaridar ba.
